File: A fuel pump. AFP/Daniel Leal JOHANNESBURG - Brace yourself for massive fuel price hikes. The Automobile Association is predicting huge increases across the board next month. READ: Massive fuel price hike expected in June A litre of petrol will cost motorists up to R1.97 more. Diesel is expected to spike by up to R1.62 while a litre of paraffin is expected to increase by a whopping R2.14. The association says international oil prices and the rand versus US dollar exchange rate are the main factors behind looming hikes.